Yves Laprie

LORIA - CNRS INRIA and Université de Lorraine

   I am CNRS senior scientist (Director of Reasearch) at LORIA UMR 7503
   which is a laboratory common to CNRS, INRIA and Lorraine University. My
   reseach is in articulatory synthesis and modeling, speech analysis and
   language learning. I am also teaching speech analysis and applied
   phonetics in master TAL of Lorraine University.

Studying in Nancy - Master and PhD

     If your are interested in studying Language processing (Traitement
   Automatique des langues) have a look on the web page of the master TAL
   of Lorraine University.

     If your are interested in studying Computer Science have a look on
   the web page of the master in computer science of Lorraine University.

     If you are interested in a master internship or in starting a PhD in
   articulatory articulatory synthesis or speech analysis do not hesitate
   to contact me or have a look on the web page of doctoral school IAEM of
   Lorraine University.

